"Are you kidding? What kind of robot is a barrel?" He put out his foot and pushed it gently.\par
"That's extremely impolite," Norby said. "Why do you let him do that, Jeff?" The robot extruded his legs and arms and struggled upright. His hat lifted, and two eyes glared furiously at Fargo. "If I kicked \i you," \i0 he said, "I'm sure you would object."\par
"What do you know?" said Fargo, sounding dumbfounded. "It \i is \i0 a robot. Where did you get it, Jeff?"\par
"At a secondhand robot store. You told me to get a teaching robot, and that's what it is. And he's my friend, mostly. Are you all right, Norby?"\par
"Yes," said Norby, "and I'm glad you think I'm your friend, even though you don't treat me like one. Surely you don't expect me to stay all right when you persist in putting us into these dangerous situations with muggers-"\par
"That's a teaching robot?" said Fargo.\par
"He sure is. He's teaching me that life is complicated and dangerous," said Jeff. "But you still haven't told me who these muggers are. Or don't you know?"\par
"Well, I don't know them by name, but I suppose they're a pair of Ing's henchmen." With his foot he prodded the smaller one, who was still groaning. "They don't seem to be badly damaged, unfortunately."\par
Suddenly the larger one grunted, opened his eyes, and rolled over, reaching for a short stick that lay in the grass.\par
Norby extended an arm farther than Jeff knew he could, grabbed the stick, and touched the henchman with it. The henchman yowled and seemed to collapse.\par
Norby threw the stick to Jeff. "Take it," he cried. \i "My \i0 sixth sense tells me you may find it useful."\par
Fargo walked over, took the stick from Jeff, and examined it closely. "Hey, what we've got here is an illegal truth wand, with a built-in stunner. That's an expensive item and a beautiful job, too. This shouldn't be available outside the Space Fleet."\par
